The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Cheap PC 

 Bangalore, Jan. 6: Intel and the Karnataka government today announced Gyanodaya, a state-assisted computer purchase programme for state employees on monthly instalment as low as Rs 399, reports our special correspondent.

 The programme aims to make government employees IT-savvy and, at the same time, bridge the digital divide by providing affordable purchase options starting at Rs 13,000. 

 The partners for the project are Microsoft and hardware makers HCL, HP and PCS.

 Karnataka chief minister Dharam Singh said the programme will help develop higher skill levels and a better informed workforce. 




